{
  "doc_id": "prion_0516",
  "text": "A case of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease of cerebellar type is reported.\nIn this case the cerebellar cortex exhibited classical Kuru-plaques.\nFrom a comparison of this finding with 50 cerebella from senile patients and patients with cerebellar atrophies it is concluded that the Kuru-plaque is specific for Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease, possible even for its cerebellar variant.",
